-- Article 6: Net Worth Tracking Without Bank Sync
-- ============================================================
(1,
'How to Track Your Net Worth for Free (No Bank Sync, No Risk)',
'net-worth-tracker-no-bank-sync',
'Knowing your net worth is the single most motivating number in personal finance. Here is how to calculate and track it manually every month — without connecting a single account.',
'/public/blog/net-worth.png',
'Person calculating assets and liabilities in a notebook',
'published',
'[
  {"type":"paragraph","text":"Net worth is the one number that tells the full story of your financial health. Not your salary, not your savings account balance, not your credit score — your net worth. It is what you own minus what you owe. And tracking it monthly is the fastest way to stay motivated about your finances."},
  {"type":"heading","text":"What Is Net Worth?"},
  {"type":"paragraph","text":"Net worth = Total Assets − Total Liabilities. Assets are things you own that have value. Liabilities are debts you owe. A positive net worth means you own more than you owe. A negative net worth — common early in life — simply means debt currently outweighs assets. Tracking it shows you the direction of travel."},
  {"type":"heading","text":"Step 1: List Your Assets"},
  {"type":"paragraph","text":"Go through everything you own that has monetary value:"},
  {"type":"list","items":["Checking and savings account balances","Investment accounts (stocks, ETFs, crypto)","Retirement accounts (401k, IRA, pension value)","Property value (current market estimate)","Vehicle value (use a used-car site for current market value)","Other valuables: jewellery, collectibles, business equity"]},
  {"type":"heading","text":"Step 2: List Your Liabilities"},
  {"type":"list","items":["Mortgage balance outstanding","Car loan balance","Student loan balance","Credit card balances","Personal loans","Any other debt"]},
  {"type":"heading","text":"Step 3: Calculate and Record"},
  {"type":"paragraph","text":"Subtract total liabilities from total assets. Record this number in a notebook, spreadsheet, or your SpendScribe notes section. Date it. That is your baseline."},
  {"type":"heading","text":"How Often Should You Update It?"},
  {"type":"paragraph","text":"Monthly is ideal — it gives you enough data points to see trends without the noise of week-to-week market fluctuations. Do your net worth update on the same day as your monthly budget reset for maximum efficiency."},
  {"type":"heading","text":"Why Manual Tracking Is More Powerful Than Automated"},
  {"type":"paragraph","text":"When you manually enter your asset values and debt balances each month, you engage with the numbers. You notice that your car has depreciated $800 since last month. You notice that your student loan is finally below $20,000. You notice your investment account grew by $1,200. Automated syncing shows you the same data — but because you did not touch it, you do not feel it."},
  {"type":"heading","text":"The Motivating Power of Watching Net Worth Grow"},
  {"type":"paragraph","text":"Early on, net worth growth feels slow. Paying off $200 of credit card debt while living costs consume the rest of your income does not feel transformative. But plotted on a chart over 12 months, the line goes up. That visual proof of progress is what keeps people committed to budgeting when motivation fades."},
  {"type":"heading","text":"No Bank Sync Means No Security Risk"},
  {"type":"paragraph","text":"Every app that syncs your bank account holds credentials or tokens that could be compromised. Manual net worth tracking requires zero shared access. You calculate the numbers yourself from your own accounts and enter them yourself. There is nothing to breach."},
  {"type":"paragraph","text":"Your net worth is your financial scoreboard. You do not need an app with read access to your bank to keep score. A notebook and 10 minutes once a month is all it takes."}
]',
'net worth,savings,manual tracking,financial health,privacy',
'Track Your Net Worth for Free Without Bank Sync | SpendScribe',
'Learn how to calculate and track your net worth manually every month — no bank connection, no security risk, and more motivating than automated tools.',
'net worth tracker, track net worth, calculate net worth, personal net worth, net worth without bank sync',
7,
NOW(), NOW(), NOW());
